text.__SUMMARY__:
Acacia chapmanii is a shrub of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Plurinerves. It is native to an area in the Wheatbelt  region of Western Australia.The shrub typically grows to a height of 0.3 to 2 metres (1 to 7 ft). It blooms from August to September and produces yellow flowers.
There are two recognised subspecies:

Acacia chapmanii subsp. australis
Acacia chapmanii subsp. chapmanii
